SENATE BILL DRS35114-NB-57
Short Title: Funeral Board Transportation Agreements/Ins. (Public)
Sponsors: Senator Johnson (Primary Sponsor).
Referred to:
1 A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
2 AN ACT TO MODIFY THE REQUIREMENTS OF TRANSPORTATION PROTECTION
3 AGREEMENTS PROVIDED BY CERTAIN FUNERAL SERVICE PROVIDERS.
4 The General Assembly of North Carolina enacts:
5 SECTION 1.(a) G.S. 90-210.60 reads as rewritten:
6 "§ 90-210.60. Definitions.
7 As used in this Article, unless the context requires otherwise:
8 …
9 (5) "Preneed funeral contract" means any contract, agreement, or mutual
10 understanding, or any series or combination of contracts, agreements, or
11 mutual understandings, whether funded by trust deposits or prearrangement
12 insurance policies, or any combination thereof, which has for a purpose the
13 furnishing or performance of funeral services, or the furnishing or delivery of
14 personal property, merchandise, or services of any nature in connection with
15 the final disposition of a dead human body, to be furnished or delivered at a
16 time determinable by the death of the person whose body is to be disposed of,
17 but does not mean the furnishing of a cemetery lot, crypt, niche, or
18 mausoleum;mausoleum. This term does not include a transportation
19 protection agreement.
20 …
21 (10) "Transportation protection agreement" means an agreement that primarily
22 provides for the coordination and arranging of all professional services related
23 to the preparation of human remains or cremated remains for the purpose of
24 initial and subsequent transportation of those remains."
25 SECTION 1.(b) G.S. 90-210.72 reads as rewritten:
26 "§ 90-210.72. Nonapplication to certain funeral contracts.
27 This Article does not apply to contracts any of the following:
28 (1) Contracts for funeral services or merchandise sold as preneed burial insurance
29 policies pursuant to Part 13 of Article 10 of Chapter 143B of the North
30 Carolina General Statutes or to replacements policies pursuant to Article 13E
31 of this Chapter.
32 (2) Replacements or conversions of such policies pursuant to G.S.
33 143B-472.28.G.S. 90-210.106.
34 (3) A transportation protection agreement as defined in this Article."
35 SECTION 1.(c) The North Carolina Board of Funeral Service may adopt rules to
36 implement the provisions of this section.
