1 SECTION 2.(a) G.S. 58-7-15 reads as rewritten:
2 "§ 58-7-15. Kinds of insurance authorized.
3 The kinds of insurance that may be authorized in this State, subject to the other provisions of
4 Articles 1 through 64 of this Chapter, are set forth in this section. Except to the extent an insurer
5 participates in a risk sharing plan under Article 42 of this Chapter, nothing in this section requires
6 any insurer to insure every kind of risk that it is authorized to insure. Except to the extent an
7 insurer participates in a risk sharing plan under Article 42 of this Chapter, no insurer may transact
8 any other business than that specified in its charter and articles of association or incorporation.
9 The power to do any kind of insurance against loss of or damage to property includes the power
10 to insure all lawful interests in the property and to insure against loss of use and occupancy and
11 rents and profits resulting therefrom; but no kind of insurance includes life insurance or insurance
12 against legal liability for personal injury or death unless specified in this section. In addition to
13 any power to engage in any other kind of business than an insurance business that is specifically
14 conferred by the provisions of Articles 1 through 64 of this Chapter, any insurer authorized to do
15 business in this State may engage in such other kinds of business to the extent necessarily or
16 properly incidental to the kinds of insurance business that it is authorized to do in this State. Each
17 of the following indicates the scope of the kind of insurance business specified:
18 (1) "Life insurance", meaning every insurance upon the lives of human beings
19 and every insurance appertaining thereto. The business of life insurance
20 includes the granting of endowment benefits; additional benefits in the event
21 of death by accident or accidental means; additional benefits operating to
22 safeguard the contract from lapse, or to provide a special surrender value, in
23 the event of total and permanent disability of the insured, including industrial
24 sick benefit; and optional modes of settlement of proceeds. The business of
25 life insurance does not include the provision of transportation protection
26 agreements, as defined under G.S. 90-210.60.
27 …."
28 SECTION 2.(b) G.S. 58-58-1 reads as rewritten:
29 "§ 58-58-1. Definitions; requisites of contract.
30 (a) All corporations or associations doing business in this State, under any charter or
31 statute of this or any other state, involving the payment of money or other thing of value to
32 families or representatives of policy and certificate holders or members, conditioned upon the
33 continuance or cessation of human life, or involving an insurance, guaranty, contract, or pledge
34 for the payment of endowments or annuities, or who employ agents to solicit such business, are
35 life insurance companies, in all respects subject to the laws herein made and provided for the
36 government of life insurance companies, and shall not make any such insurance, guaranty,
37 contract, or pledge in this State with any citizen, or resident thereof, which does not distinctly
38 state the amount of benefits payable, the manner of payment, the consideration therefor and such
39 other provisions as the Commissioner may require.
40 (b) This section does not apply to a preneed licensee under Article 13D of Chapter 90 of
41 the General Statutes or for the purposes of a transportation agreement, as defined under
42 G.S. 90-210.60."
43 SECTION 2.(c) G.S. 58-58-125 reads as rewritten:
44 "§ 58-58-125. Minimum premium rates for assessment life insurance companies.
45 No assessment life insurance corporation, organization or association of any kind issuing
46 policies or contracts upon the life of any resident of this State shall hereafter be organized or
47 licensed by the Commissioner unless such corporation, organization or association adopt
48 premium rates based upon the attained age of the assured at the time of issuance of the contract
49 and such rates shall not be less than those fixed by the American Experience Table of Mortality
50 or any other recognized table of mortality approved by the Commissioner. Nothing contained in
51 this section shall be construed to affect burial associations regulated under G.S. 143B-472
