11 SECTION 2.(e) G.S. 58-58-335(8) reads as rewritten:
12 "(8) "Life insurance" means insurance coverage on human lives, including benefits
13 of endowment and annuities, and may include benefits in the event of death
14 or dismemberment by accident and benefits for disability income; and unless
15 otherwise specifically excluded, includes individually issued annuities. In
16 accordance with G.S. 58-7-15, this term does not include a transportation
17 protection agreement."
18 SECTION 2.(f) G.S. 58-60-35(a) reads as rewritten:
19 "§ 58-60-35. Disclosure of prearrangement insurance policy provisions.
20 (a) As used The following definitions apply in this section:
21 (1) "Prearrangement" means any Prearrangement. – A contract, agreement, or
22 mutual understanding, or any series or combination of contracts, agreements
23 or mutual understandings, whether funded by trust deposits or prearrangement
24 insurance policies, or any combination thereof, which has for a purpose the
25 furnishing or performance of specific funeral services, or the furnishing or
26 delivery of specific personal property, merchandise, or services of any nature
27 in connection with the final disposition of a dead human body, to be furnished
28 or delivered at a time determinable by the death of the person whose body is
29 to be disposed of, but does not mean the furnishing of a cemetery lot, crypt,
30 niche, mausoleum, grave marker or monument. This term does not include a
31 transportation protection agreement, as defined under G.S. 90-210.60.
32 (2) "Prearrangement insurance policy" means a Prearrangement insurance policy.
33 – A life insurance policy, annuity contract, or other insurance contract, or any
34 series of contracts or agreements in any form or manner, issued on a group or
35 individual basis by an insurance company authorized by law to do business in
36 this State, which, whether by assignment or otherwise, has for its sole purpose
37 the funding of a specific preneed funeral contract or a specific
38 insurance-funded funeral or burial prearrangement, the insured being the
39 person for whose service the funds were paid."
40 SECTION 3. This act becomes effective October 1, 2025, and applies to preneed
41 funeral contracts and transportation protection agreements entered into on or after that date.
